  <title><cmdname>setting-audit</cmdname></title>
  <shortdesc>Configures the audit settings.</shortdesc>
  <refbody>
    <section><title>Syntax</title>
      <p>The basic syntax is:</p>
      <codeblock outputclass="language-bash">couchbase-cli setting-audit -c [host]:8091 -u [admin] -p [password] [options]</codeblock>
    </section> <section><title>Description</title>
      <p> Use this command to set various options for audits.</p>
      
      
      
    </section>
    
    <section>
      <title>Options</title>
      <p>The following are the command options:</p>
      <table><title>setting-audit options</title>
        <tgroup cols="2">
          <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.64*"/>
          <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="1*"/>
          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry>Option</entry>
              <entry>Description</entry>
            </row>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry><codeph>--audit-log-rotate-interval=[MINUTES]</codeph></entry>
              <entry>Log rotation interval in minutes.</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry><codeph>--audit-log-path=[PATH]</codeph></entry>
              <entry>Target log directory (required).</entry>
            </row>
            <row>
              <entry><codeph>--audit-enabled=[0|1]</codeph></entry>
              <entry>Audit enable (yes=1, no=0).</entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </table>
      
    </section>
    
    <section>
      <title>Examples</title>
      
      
      <p><b>Enable audit with the log, specify the rotating interval, and post the logs in a
          specified directory</b></p>
      <codeblock outputclass="language-bash">couchbase-cli setting-audit -c 192.168.0.1:8091 -u Administrator -p password --audit-enabled=1 --audit-log-rotate-interval=15 --audit-log-path=../../logs</codeblock>
      <p><b>Response</b></p> <codeblock>SUCCESS: set audit settings</codeblock> 
     
      <p><b>Enable audit with the log and specify the rotating interval</b></p>
      <codeblock outputclass="language-bash">couchbase-cli setting-audit -c 192.168.0.1:8091 -u Administrator -p password --audit-enabled=1 --audit-log-rotate-interval=15</codeblock>
      <p><b>Response</b></p><codeblock>ERROR: unable to set audit settings (400) Bad Request
        {"errors":{"logPath":"The value must be a valid directory"}}</codeblock>
      <p>The log directory has to be set.</p>
    </section>
  
